[0.005, "o", "\u001b[H; The index name (concatenated with the prefix) in $_SESSION\r\n; containing the upload progress information\u001b[3;3HDefault Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\u001b[22X\u001b[4;3HDevelopment Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\u001b[10X\u001b[5;3HProduction Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.name\r\n;session.upload_progress.name = \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[9;3HHow frequently the upload progress should be updated.\r\n; Given either in percentages (per-file), or in bytes\r\n; Default Value: \"1%\"\u001b[12;3HDevelopment Value: \"1%\"\u001b[18X\u001b[13;3HProduction Value: \"1%\"\u001b[25X\u001b[14;3Hhttps://php.net/session.upload-progress.freq\u001b[15;2Hsession.upload_progress.freq =  \"1%\"\u001b[11X\r\n\u001b[39X\u001b[17;3HThe minimum delay between updates, in seconds\u001b[6X\u001b[18;3HDefault Value: 1\u001b[18X\u001b[19;3HDevelopment Value: 1\u001b[32X\u001b[20;3HProduction Value: 1\u001b[41X\u001b[21;6Hps://php.net/session.upload-progress.min-freq\r\n;session.upload_progress.min_freq = \"1\"\u001b[24;3HOnly write session data when session data is changed. Enabled by default.\u001b[25;3Hhttps://php.net/session.lazy-write\u001b[28X\u001b[26;2Hsession.lazy_write = On\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[65X\n\u001b[96m[Assertion]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[14X\u001b[29;3HSwitch whether to compile assertions at all (to have no overhead at run-time)\u001b[30;3H-1: Do not compile at all\u001b[24X\u001b[31;3H 0: Jump over assertion at run-time\u001b[18X\u001b[32;3H 1: Execute assertions\u001b[30X\u001b[33;3HChanging from or to a negative value is only \u001b[30m\u001b[103mpo\u001b[m\u000fssible in php.ini!\r\n; (For turning assertions on and off at run-time, toggle zend.assertions between the values 1 and 0)\r\n; Default Value: 1\u001b[36;3HDevelopment Value: 1\u001b[35X\u001b[37;3HProduction Value: -1\u001b[49X\u001b[38;3Hhttps://php.net/zend.assertions\r\nzend.assertions =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[54X\r\n\u001b[36X\n\u001b[96m[COM]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[60X\u001b[42;3Hpath to a file containing GUIDs, IIDs or filenames of files with TypeLibs\u001b[43;3Hhttps://php.net/com.typelib-file\u001b[18X\u001b[44;2Hcom.typelib_file =\r\n\u001b[23X\u001b[46;3Hallow Distributed-COM calls\u001b[47;2H https://php.net/com.allow-dcom\r\n;com.allow_dcom = true\r\n\u001b[46X\u001b[50;3Hautoregister constants of a com\u001b[30m\u001b[103mpo\u001b[m\u000fnent's typelib on com_load()\u001b[51;3Hhttps://php.net/com.autoregister-typelib\u001b[52;2Hcom.autoregister_typelib = true\r\n\u001b[49X\u001b[54;2H register constants casesensitive   \r\n; https://php.net/com.autoregister-casesensitive\u001b[56;2Hcom.autoregister_casesensitive = false\u001b[34X\r\n\u001b[26X\u001b[58;3Hshow warnings on duplicate constant registrations\u001b[59;3Hhttps://php.net/com.autoregister-verbose\u001b[60;2Hcom.autoregister_verbose = true\r\n\u001b[49X\u001b[62;2H The default character set code-page to use when passing strings to and from COM objects.\r\n; Default: system ANSI code page\u001b[64;2Hcom.code_page=\u001b[41X\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[66;224H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f501,48        81\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
