[0.005, "o", "\u001b[Hsession.referer_check =\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[74X\u001b[3;3HSet to {nocache,private,public,} to determine HTTP caching aspects\u001b[7X\u001b[4;3Hor leave this empty to avoid sending anti-caching headers.\u001b[19X\u001b[5;3Hhttps://php.net/session.cache-limiter\u001b[38X\r\nsession.cache_limiter =\u001b[92m nocache\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[50X\u001b[8;3HDocument expires after n minutes.\u001b[9;19Hsession.cache-expire\r\nsession.cache_expire = 180\u001b[12;3Htrans sid support is disabled by default.\u001b[35X\u001b[13;3HUse of trans sid may risk your users' security.\u001b[22X\u001b[14;3HUse this option with caution.\u001b[47X\u001b[15;3H- User may send URL contains active session ID\u001b[30X\u001b[16;3H  to other person via. email/irc/etc. \u001b[17;3H- URL that contains active session ID may be stored\r\n;   in publicly accessible computer.\r\n; - User may access your site with the same session ID\u001b[20;3H  always using URL stored in browser's history or bookmarks.\u001b[21;3Hhttps://php.net/session.use-trans-sid\r\nsession.use_trans_sid = 0\u001b[54X\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[24;3HThe URL rewriter will look for URLs in a defined set of HTML tags.\u001b[10X\u001b[25;3H<form> is special; if you include them here, the rewriter will\u001b[14X\u001b[26;3Hadd a hidden <input> field with the info which is otherwise appended\u001b[27;2H to URLs. <form> tag's action attribute URL will not be modified\r\n; unless it is specified.\u001b[29;3HNote that all valid entries require a \"=\", even if no value follows.\u001b[30;3HDefault Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[26X\u001b[31;3HDevelopment Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[32;3HProduction Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\r\n; https://php.net/url-rewriter.tags\r\nsession.trans_sid_tags =\u001b[92m \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[46X\u001b[36;3HURL rewriter does not rewrite absolute URLs by default.\r\n; To enable rewrites for absolute paths, target hosts must be specified\r\n; at RUNTIME. i.e. use ini_set()\u001b[39;3H<form> tags is special. PHP will check action attribute's URL regardless\u001b[40;3Hof session.trans_sid_tags setting.\r\n; If no host is defined, HTTP_HOST will be used for allowed host.\r\n; Example value: php.net,www.php.net,wiki.php.net\u001b[43;3HUse \",\" for multiple hosts. No spaces are allowed.\u001b[24X\u001b[44;3HDefault Value: \"\"\u001b[23X\u001b[45;2H Development Value: \"\"\u001b[46;4Hroduction Value: \"\"\u001b[34X\u001b[47;2Hsession.trans_sid_hosts=\"\"\u001b[7X\r\n\u001b[30X\n; Enable upload progress tracking in $_SESSION\u001b[50;3HDefault Value: On\u001b[27X\u001b[51;3HDevelopment Value: On\u001b[10X\r\n; Production Value: On   \r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.enabled\u001b[54;2Hsession.upload_progress.enabled = On\u001b[13X\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[56;3HCleanup the progress information as soon as all POST data has been read\u001b[57;2H (i.e. upload completed).\r\n; Default Value: On\u001b[59;3HDevelopment Value: On\u001b[24X\u001b[60;3HProduction Value: On\u001b[14X\u001b[61;19Hsession.upload-progress.cleanup\u001b[62;2Hsession.upload_progress.cleanup = On\u001b[64;3HA prefix used for the upload progress key in $_SESSION\u001b[65;3HDefault Value: \"upload_progress_\" \u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f1463,1         77\u001b[67;14H\u001b[?25h"]
[1.231, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \b"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[H; is invoked. $argc contains an integer representing the number of arguments\r\n; that were passed when the script was invoked. These arrays are extremely\u001b[3;3Huseful when running scripts from the command line. When this directive is\u001b[4;3Henabled, registering these variables consumes CPU cycles and memory each time\u001b[5;3Ha script is executed. For security reasons, this feature should be disabled\r\n; for non-CLI SAPIs.\u001b[11X\r\n; Note: This directive is ignored for the CLI SAPI\u001b[8;3HThis directive is deprecated.    \u001b[9;19Hregister-argc-argv  \r\n;register_argc_argv = Off \u001b[12;3HWhen enabled, the ENV, REQUEST and SERVER variables are created when they're\u001b[13;3Hfirst used (Just In Time) instead of when the script starts. If these\u001b[14;3Hvariables are not used within a script, having this directive on will result\u001b[15;3Hin a performance gain. The PHP directive register_argc_argv must be disabled\u001b[16;3Hfor this directive to have any effect.\u001b[17;3Hhttps://php.net/auto-globals-jit\u001b[19X\r\nauto_globals_jit =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[54X\u001b[20;3HWhether PHP will read the POST data.\u001b[24X\u001b[21;3HThis option is enabled by default.   \r\n; Most likely, you won't want to disable this option globally. It causes $_POST\r\n; and $_FILES to always be empty; the only way you will be able to read the\u001b[24;3HPOST data will be through the php://input stream wrapper. This can be useful\u001b[25;3Hto proxy requests or to process the POST data in a memory efficient fashion.\u001b[26;3Hhttps://php.net/enable-post-data-reading\u001b[28X\u001b[27;2Henable_post_data_reading = Off\u001b[34X\r\n\u001b[25X\u001b[29;3HMaximum size of POST data that PHP will accept.\u001b[21X\u001b[30;3HIts value may be 0 to disable the limit. It is ignored if POST data reading\u001b[31;3His disabled through enable_post_data_reading.\u001b[8X\u001b[32;3Hhttps://php.net/post-max-size\u001b[23X\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mpost_max_si\u001b[m\u000fze =\u001b[92m 8M\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[17X\r\n\u001b[59X\n; Automatically add files before PHP document.\u001b[36;3Hhttps://php.net/auto-prepend-file\u001b[22X\r\nauto_prepend_file =\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[32X\u001b[39;3HAutomatically add files after PHP document.\u001b[29X\u001b[40;3Hhttps://php.net/auto-append-file  \r\nauto_append_file =\u001b[47X\r\n\u001b[49X\u001b[43;3HBy default, PHP will output a media type using the Content-Type header. To\u001b[44;3Hdisable this, simply set it to be empty.\u001b[45;2H\u001b[22X\u001b[46;4HHP's built-in default media type is set to text/html.\u001b[47;2H https://php.net/default-mimetype\r\ndefault_mimetype =\u001b[92m \"text/html\"\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[46X\u001b[50;3HPHP's default character set is set to UTF-8.\u001b[51;3Hhttps://php.net/default-charset\r\ndefault_charset =\u001b[92m \"UTF-8\"\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[49X\u001b[54;2H PHP internal character encoding is set to empty.\r\n; If empty, default_charset is used.\u001b[56;3Hhttps://php.net/internal-encoding\u001b[38X\u001b[57;2Hinternal_encoding =\u001b[6X\r\n\u001b[19X\u001b[59;3HPHP input character encoding is set to empty.\u001b[60;3HIf empty, default_charset is used.\u001b[61;19Hinput-encoding\u001b[17X\u001b[62;2Hinput_encoding =\u001b[20X\u001b[64;3HPHP output character encoding is set to empty.\u001b[8X\u001b[65;3HIf empty, default_charset is used.\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f693,1          36\u001b[67;13H\u001b[?25h"]
