[0.005, "o", "\u001b[1;59H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000fmber of arg\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[3;3Hu\u001b[m\u000fsef\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000fl when r\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[4;44Hu\u001b[5;19Hu\u001b[m\u000fted. For sec\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000frity reasons, this feat\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000fre sho\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[13;9Hu\u001b[m\u000fsed (J\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[14;21Hu\u001b[m\u000fsed within a script, having this directive on will res\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[15;64Hu\u001b[17;20Hu\u001b[18;2Hu\u001b[21;33Hu\u001b[22;18Hu\u001b[m\u000f won't want to disable this option globally. It ca\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[23;50Hu\u001b[24;25Hu\u001b[m\u000fgh the php://inp\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000ft stream wrapper. This can be \u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000fsef\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[25;15Hu\u001b[29;8Hu\u001b[30;10Hu\u001b[31;19Hu\r\n\n\u001b[m\u000fpost_max_si\u001b[35;4H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000ftomatically add files before PHP doc\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[36;20Hu\u001b[37;2Hu\u001b[39;4Hu\u001b[m\u000ftomatically add files after PHP doc\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[40;20Hu\u001b[41;2Hu\u001b[43;10Hu\u001b[m\u000flt, PHP will o\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000ftp\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[m\u000ft a media type \u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[46;10Hu\u001b[m\u000filt-in defa\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\nu\u001b[48;5Hu\u001b[50;13Hu\u001b[51;23Hu\u001b[52;5Hu\u001b[55;17Hu\u001b[m\u000flt_charset is \u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[59;10Hu\u001b[60;17Hu\u001b[m\u000flt_charset is \u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[61;22Hu\u001b[62;5Hu\u001b[64;8Hu\u001b[m\u000ftp\u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[65;17Hu\u001b[m\u000flt_charset is \u001b[30m\u001b[103mu\u001b[66;225H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f5,4 \u001b[67;3H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.167, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000fp"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[Hextension_dir =\u001b[92m \"/usr/lib/php/modules/\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[37X\u001b[2;3HOn windows:\u001b[61X\u001b[3;2Hextension_dir = \"ext\"\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[79X\u001b[5;3HDirectory where the temporary files should be placed.\u001b[22X\u001b[6;3HDefaults to the system default (see sys_get_temp_dir)\u001b[7;2Hsys_temp_dir = \"/tmp\"\u001b[28X\r\n\u001b[31X\u001b[9;3HWhether or not to enable the dl() function.  The dl() function does NOT work\u001b[10;2H properly in multithreaded servers, such as IIS or Zeus, and is automatically\r\n; disabled on them.\u001b[12;3Hhttps://php.net/enable-dl\u001b[51X\r\nenable_dl =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[56X\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[15;3Hcgi.force_redirect is necessary to provide security running PHP as a CGI under\u001b[16;3Hmost web servers.  Left undefined, PHP turns this on by default.  You can\u001b[17;3Hturn it off here AT YOUR OWN RISK\r\n; **You CAN safely turn this off for IIS, in fact, you MUST.**\r\n; https://php.net/cgi.force-redirect\u001b[20;2Hcgi.force_redirect = 1\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[22;3Hif cgi.nph is enabled it will force cgi to always sent Status: 200 with\u001b[6X\u001b[23;3Hevery request. PHP's default behavior is to disable this feature.\u001b[8X\u001b[24;2Hcgi.nph = 1\u001b[66X\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[26;3Hif cgi.force_redirect is turned on, and you are not running under Apache or Netscape\u001b[27;2H (iPlanet) web servers, you MAY need to set an environment variable name that PHP\r\n; will look for to know it is OK to continue execution.  Setting this variable MAY\u001b[29;3Hcause security issues, KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING FIRST.\u001b[30;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.redirect-status-env\u001b[36X\u001b[31;2Hcgi.redirect_status_env =\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[31X\n; cgi.fix_pathinfo provides *real* PATH_INFO/PATH_TRANSLATED s\u001b[30m\u001b[103mup\u001b[m\u000fport for CGI.  PHP's\r\n; previous behaviour was to set PATH_TRANSLATED to SCRIPT_FILENAME, and to not grok\u001b[35;3Hwhat PATH_INFO is.  For more information on PATH_INFO, see the cgi specs.  Setting\u001b[36;3Hthis to 1 will cause PHP CGI to fix its paths to conform to the spec.  A setting\r\n; of zero causes PHP to behave as before.  Default is 1.  You should fix your scripts\r\n; to use SCRIPT_FILENAME rather than PATH_TRANSLATED.\u001b[39;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.fix-pathinfo\u001b[11X\u001b[40;2Hcgi.fix_pathinfo=1\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[18X\n; if cgi.discard_path is enabled, the PHP CGI binary can safely be placed outside\u001b[43;3Hof the web tree and people will not be able to circumvent .htaccess security.\u001b[44;2Hcgi.discard_path=1\u001b[23X\r\n \u001b[46;3HFastCGI under IIS s\u001b[30m\u001b[103mup\u001b[m\u000fports the ability to impersonate \u001b[47;3Hsecurity tokens of the calling client.  This allows IIS to define the\r\n; security context that the request runs under.  mod_fastcgi under Apache\r\n; does not currently s\u001b[30m\u001b[103mup\u001b[m\u000fport this feature (03/17/2002)\u001b[50;3HSet to 1 if running under IIS.  Default is zero.\u001b[51;19Hfastcgi.impersonate\r\n;fastcgi.impersonate = 1 \u001b[54;4Hrevent decoding of SCRIPT_FILENAME when using Apache ProxyPass or\u001b[55;3HProxyPassMatch. This should be used if script file paths are not stored\u001b[56;3Hin an encoded format on the file system.\u001b[57;2H Default is 1.\u001b[5X\r\n;fastcgi.script_path_encoded = 0\r\n\u001b[47X\u001b[60;3HDisable logging through FastCGI connection. PHP's default behavior is to enable\u001b[61;3Hthis feature.\u001b[17X\u001b[62;2Hfastcgi.logging = 0\u001b[64;3Hcgi.rfc2616_headers configuration option tells PHP what type of headers to\u001b[65;3Huse when sending HTTP response code. If set to 0, PHP sends Status: header that\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f790,63         41\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
